{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17566887","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17566887"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T23:50:19+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T23:50:19+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18901"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18901","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18901"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.02,0.93,0.02,0.02,0.02]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11634"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80111"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11634","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11634"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18901"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65388"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"17"},{"type":"tags","id":"18"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"11260"},{"type":"tags","id":"11347"},{"type":"tags","id":"11348"},{"type":"tags","id":"11349"},{"type":"tags","id":"12867"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"27369"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27370"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80111","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/80111"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 42-year-old woman presents to discuss management options for her newly diagnosed hypertension. Her blood pressure is consistently 150/95 mmHg. She is hesitant about starting medication and expresses interest in lifestyle modifications first. The doctor provides information about both approaches, discusses the evidence for each option, and explores the patient\u0027s preferences and concerns.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best demonstrates appropriate shared decision-making in this scenario?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Insisting on medication as it is evidence-based practice","Exploring patient values while explaining treatment options","Referring to another doctor for a second opinion","Providing written information and asking the patient to decide alone","Deferring all decisions to patient preference"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct approach involves \u003Cstrong\u003Eexploring patient values while explaining treatment options\u003C/strong\u003E. Shared decision-making requires healthcare providers to actively engage with patients, presenting balanced information about available options while considering the patient\u0027s values, preferences, and circumstances.\u003C/p\u003E        \u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect approaches are problematic because:\u003C/p\u003E        \u003Cul\u003E        \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EInsisting on medication as it is evidence-based practice\u003C/strong\u003E - This paternalistic approach ignores patient autonomy and preferences\u003C/li\u003E                \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EProviding written information and asking the patient to decide alone\u003C/strong\u003E - This abandons the \u0027shared\u0027 aspect of decision-making and may overwhelm the patient\u003C/li\u003E                \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EReferring to another doctor for a second opinion\u003C/strong\u003E - While sometimes appropriate, this avoids the responsibility of engaging in shared decision-making\u003C/li\u003E                \u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDeferring all decisions to patient preference\u003C/strong\u003E - This fails to provide professional expertise and guidance needed for informed decision-making\u003C/li\u003E    \u003C/ul\u003E        \u003Cp\u003EEffective shared decision-making involves a collaborative dialogue where medical expertise is combined with patient values and preferences to reach decisions that are both evidence-based and aligned with patient goals.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Shared decision-making involves actively engaging patients in healthcare decisions by discussing options, benefits, and risks.","Patient values and preferences are central to shared decision-making and should guide treatment choices.","Healthcare providers must present balanced information in an understandable way to support informed decision-making."],"references":["Montori VM, Ruissen MM, Hargraves IG, Brito JP, Kunneman M. Shared decision-making as a method of care. BMJ Evid Based Med. 2023 Aug;28(4):213-217. doi: 10.1136/bmjebm-2022-112068. Epub 2022 Dec 2. PMID: 36460328; PMCID: PMC10423463. Available from: https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC10423463/","Medical Board of Australia. Good medical practice: a code of conduct for doctors in Australia [online]. 2020 [Cited 2025 Jan 15]. Available at: https://www.medicalboard.gov.au/codes-guidelines-policies/code-of-conduct.aspx"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65388"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18901"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65388","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/65388"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-17T13:03:13+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-17T13:03:43+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11634"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80111"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"17","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/17"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\ude07","name":"Bioethics","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagG